VIABILITY
Digital Margiela is viable because it combines both digital and physical experiences into one subscription service. Magazine readers and vintage collectors already spend money on rare fashion publications, making a subscription model realistic and sustainable. Since the MVP starts small with a focused audience of students and fashion enthusiasts, startup costs can remain manageable while testing demand. Revenue will come from monthly and yearly subscriptions, with future opportunities including brand partnerships, advertisements, featured artist promotions, and exclusive collaborations with fashion magazines and independent creators. 


SCALABILITY
Phase 1(now): Start with students currently at pace, and mainly have student work (Fusion Magazine, Pace Press, etc.)
Phase 2 (6 months):  Branch out to Manhattan, reach out to different stores that deal with regular magazines ( Casa Magazines, Iconic Magazines, SoHo Magazines, etc.)
Phase 3 (12 months): Branch out to all of NYC, reach out to well-known brands ( Vogue, Elle, T Magazine, etc.)

